    "title" : "Generating Documentation for Hosting Online"
  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "anchor" : "Overview",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Overview",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "By default, the Swift-DocC plugin will generate an index of content that is useful for IDE’s,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "like Xcode, to render a navigator of all included documentation in the archive. Since this index",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "isn’t relevant when hosting online, you can pass the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--disable-indexing",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "when generating documentation thats intended for an online host.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swift package --target [target-name] generate-documentation --disable-indexing"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "You’ll likely want to pass an output path to Swift-DocC to send the relevant files",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "to a specific directory.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "content" : [
            {
              "inlineContent" : [
                {
                  "text" : "Remember to pass the ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "code" : "--allow-writing-to-directory",
                  "type" : "codeVoice"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " flag",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : " ",
                  "type" : "text"
                },
                {
                  "text" : "to include that directory in the SwiftPM sandboxing environment for the Swift-DocC plugin.",
                  "type" : "text"
                }
              ],
              "type" : "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "style" : "important",
          "type" : "aside"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swift package --target [target-name] \\ ",
            "    --allow-writing-to-directory [output-directory-path] \\ ",
            "    generate-documentation --disable-indexing \\",
            "    --output-path [output-directory-path]"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The files at the passed ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "[output-directory-path]",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " are now ready to be published online. Please",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "see the documentation",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier" : "https:\/\/www.swift.org\/documentation\/docc\/distributing-documentation-to-other-developers#Host-a-Documentation-Archive-on-Your-Website",
              "isActive" : true,
              "type" : "reference"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that explains how to configure the necessary routing rules for hosting a Swift-DocC archive",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "on your local server.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "Transforming-for-Static-Hosting",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "Transforming for Static Hosting",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "Alternatively, if you’d like to avoid setting custom routing rules on your server or are",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "hosting in an environment where this isn’t possible, you can generate documentation that",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "has been transformed for static hosting.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swift package --target [target-name] \\ ",
            "    --allow-writing-to-directory [output-directory-path] \\ ",
            "    generate-documentation --disable-indexing \\",
            "    --output-path [output-directory-path] \\",
            "    --transform-for-static-hosting"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This addition of the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--transform-for-static-hosting",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " flag removes the need of setting",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "any custom routing rules on your website, as long as you’re hosting the documentation",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "at the root of your website. If you’d like to host your documentation at a sub-path, you",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "can use the ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "code" : "--hosting-base-path",
              "type" : "codeVoice"
            },
            {
              "text" : " argument.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code" : [
            "$ swift package --target [target-name] \\ ",
            "    --allow-writing-to-directory [output-directory-path] \\ ",
            "    generate-documentation --disable-indexing \\",
            "    --output-path [output-directory-path] \\",
            "    --transform-for-static-hosting \\",
            "    --hosting-base-path [hosting-base-path]"
          ],
          "syntax" : "shell",
          "type" : "codeListing"
        }
      ],
      "kind" : "content"
    }
